<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">703.94/4830: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-19T13:00:00+08:00">March 19, 1932—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 19—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Joint situation report number 11, March 19th: <pb facs="0708" n="604" xml:id="pg_604"/>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <list>
                                    <item>“1. Embarkation of one Japanese mixed brigade for Japan
                                        continues.</item>
                                    <item>2. Commander 19th Route Army protests to neutral observers
                                        against the continued flights of Japanese aircraft beyond
                                        the <persName corresp="#p_SGY1">Shirakawa</persName> patrol
                                        zone. Reports from Chinese sources that civilians have been
                                        injured owing to fire from aeroplanes have not been
                                        verified.”</item>
                                </list></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>